parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause a fire.
symptoms: the dashboard lights do not come on
the vehicle makes a loud bursting sound when started
smoke appears from the steering wheel or dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Pass Lock security system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The security light comes on and off
the vehicle thinks it is being stolen and does not allow gasoline to flow to the fuel injectors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle cuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, while unexpected deployment can cause accidents, injuries, or distractions.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning airbag sensors can cause unexpected airbag deployment, leading to accidents, injuries, or distractions, or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag deployment for no apparent reason
airbag failure to deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag control module can cause airbag deployment failures, unexpected deployments, or warning lights to stay on, leading to accidents, injuries, or distractions.
The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potential engine failure.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The leakage of coolant from the air conditioner can cause the air conditioner to blow warm air, leading to discomfort and potential overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Alternator and Serpentine Belt Tensioner Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator and serpentine belt tensioner can cause damage to other engine components, leading to costly repairs.
The engine stalling and shutting off without warning can cause accidents, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to engine damage.
Premature brake wear and failure can lead to reduced stopping power, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Brake pads and rotors wear out excessively
brake lines crack and leak brake fluid
brake shoes need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ABS brake system can cause loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: failure of the ABS brake system causes accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line and Brake Fluid Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line cracks and brake fluid leaks can cause loss of brake pressure, reduced stopping power, and increased risk of accidents.
Brake noise and vibration can be a sign of underlying brake problems, which can lead to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: brakes bounce and create loud thumping noise at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective brake components can cause premature brake wear, reduced stopping power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: causing excessive wear and damage to brake parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Lower control arms break off from bushings
vehicle bottoms out and hits the pavement
noise from front struts when going over bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the tire to come off while driving, leading to accidents and injuries.
The malfunction of the electrical system can cause distractions, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Interior lights come on by themselves and stay on
vehicle jerks forward from stop position
